title: Wednesday, May 13, 2020

It's comforting to hear [[Doom-emacs]]'s author (Henrik Lissner) say that [[his workflow included Org-roam and Org-journal|https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/getvjq/yet_another_praise_to_doom/fpr3m95]], same as mine.

The hard part of my day shouldn't be figuring out the operating system

Some software is difficult and that's fine. [[Tinderbox]], [[Emacs]], [[TiddlyWiki]] are all less useful until the learning curve has been climbed. Efforts to remove that curve tend to also remove the ultimate usefulness of the tool. Not always, but often enough that one should be wary of the attempt. [[ref|https://lwn.net/SubscriberLink/819452/1480c3a59d3d9093/]]

Neat, my [[post about tracking time in Org mode|https://www.baty.net/2018/tracking-my-time-with-org-mode/]] made this week's [[Emacs News|https://sachachua.com/blog/2020/05/2020-05-11-emacs-news/]] by Sacha Chua. 

Looks like we're about to get an [[official tagging system|https://github.com/org-roam/org-roam/pull/604]] in [[Org-roam]]. This seems necessary and I'm looking forward to it.



